<p>
    <strong>From the college:</strong>
    <i>Middle Georgia State College offers academically outstanding students the opportunity for advanced placement and credit by examination. Interested students should contact Admissions Office for information on fees, test schedules, and required cut-off scores. Student may receive up to 40 hours of credit by any combination of AP, CLEP, or departmental examination. Credit earned by any of these means will be recorded on the student's record by course, course number, and semester hours earned. The grade of 'K' will be recorded but will not be included in the determination of the grade-point average. High-school students may obtain information about the AP program from their guidance counselors.</i>
